cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this dataset, please cite as below."
title: "doctrine-corpus: A judgment-eliciting Q&A corpus across the shimo4228 research program"
type: dataset
authors:
  - family-names: Shimomoto
    given-names: Tatsuya
    orcid: "https://orcid.org/0009-0002-6168-4162"
abstract: >
  A bilingual (EN + JA) Q&A corpus encoding the documented judgment of four
  research lines — Agent Knowledge Cycle, Contemplative Agent, Agent
  Attribution Practice, and Authorship Strategy — as judgment-eliciting
  pairs designed for LLM-mediated diffusion. The corpus is the operational
  form of Authorship Strategy Layer 4 tactic 7 (LLM-first ingest).
  It is base-model-independent and is intended as an ingredient — for
  larger instruction-tuning mixes, RAG retrieval, and human reading —
  rather than as a standalone fine-tuning package. A Stage D verification
  LoRA (Qwen3-8B-4bit, 851 examples, 300 iterations) was trained as a
  disposable probe and returned a preliminary FAIL verdict on the
  judgment-transfer rubric; the corpus retains its deliverable status
  and the LoRA was never a deposit target.
keywords:
